 heartbreaking but real risk—especially near poorly marked or unsupervised crosswalks.</li><li id=""""><strong id="""">Bullying and Violence:</strong> Injuries from physical altercations—especially when the school fails to intervene or monitor students properly—can also warrant legal action.</li></ul><p id="""">If your child has been hurt at school or on the way there, it’s important to know where to turn.</p><p id="""">‍<br></p><h2 id=""""><strong id="""">Who’s Legally Responsible?</strong><br></h2><p id="""">In <strong id="""">North Alabama</strong>, determining who is liable for a school-related injury depends on several factors. Sometimes the school district may be responsible due to negligence in supervision or unsafe premises. In other cases, a third party—like a bus company, a janitorial service, or even a product manufacturer—may be to blame.<br></p><p id="""">At <a href=""https://www.defattalaw.com/free-consultation""><strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong></a>, we investigate all possible sources of liability to ensure your family gets the compensation you deserve.</p><p id="""">‍<br></p><h2 id=""""><strong id="""">What to Do If Your Child is Injured</strong><br></h2><p id="""">If your child is hurt in a back-to-school accident, take these steps immediately:</p><ol start=""1"" id=""""><li id=""""><strong id="""">Seek Medical Attention</strong> – Even if injuries seem minor.</li><li id=""""><strong id="""">Document the Scene</strong> – Take photos, write down what happened, and gather witness names.</li><li id=""""><strong id="""">Report It</strong> – Let the school know in writing and request a copy of any incident reports.</li><li id=""""><strong id="""">Contact a Local Injury Attorney</strong> – Don’t assume the school or district will handle it properly.<br></li></ol><p id="""">‍</p><h3 id=""""><strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm Is Here for North Alabama Families</strong><br></h3><p id="""">At <strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong>, we have years of experience handling personal injury and wrongful death cases in <strong id="""">Huntsville and surrounding North Alabama communities</strong>. We understand the emotional and financial stress an injury can place on a family—especially when it involves your child.<br></p><p id="""">You don’t have to take on the school system or insurance companies alone. Let our compassionate and experienced legal team advocate for your family’s rights.<br></p><p id="""">Back-to-school season should be a time of excitement—not emergency rooms and legal confusion. If your child has been hurt in a preventable accident, reach out to <a href=""https://www.defattalaw.com/free-consultation""><strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong></a> in <strong id="""">Huntsville, Alabama</strong>. We’re here to help North Alabama families navigate these complex cases with clarity, compassion, and commitment.</p><p id="""">‍</p>",https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/656a0c175024d9fe2bb6d05f/6891238f2ec849c308e25e03_backtoschool.png,alix-defatta
