nts</strong>, stereotypes, or racial jokes made by coworkers or supervisors</li><li id="""">A sudden change in treatment after you voiced concerns about race-related issues</li><li id="""">Being <strong id="""">disciplined unfairly</strong> compared to employees of other races</li><li id="""">Getting fired shortly after filing a complaint or reporting workplace discrimination</li></ul><p id="""">These red flags aren’t just unethical—they may be illegal under federal and state law. If this sounds familiar, it’s worth taking a closer look at your situation with the help of a trusted attorney.</p><h3 id=""""><strong id="""">Retaliation Is Also Against the Law</strong></h3><p id="""">One of the most frustrating things employees face is <strong id="""">retaliation</strong>—when employers punish them for speaking up. Maybe you reported racial bias or asked for a fair opportunity, and instead of support, you got demoted, isolated, or fired. That’s not just wrong. That’s retaliation, and it violates your rights.</p><p id="""">At <strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong>, we take retaliation just as seriously as discrimination itself. If your employer tried to silence you for standing up, we’re here to speak up on your behalf.</p><h3 id=""""><strong id="""">What You Can Do—and How </strong><a href=""https://www.defattalaw.com/free-consultation""><strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong></a><strong id=""""> Helps</strong></h3><p id="""">Whether you’re in <strong id="""">Huntsville</strong> or elsewhere in <strong id="""">North Alabama</strong>, you deserve a workplace free of discrimination. You also deserve a legal team that listens, believes you, and knows how to fight for what’s right. At <strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong>, we:</p><ul id=""""><li id="""">Offer <strong id="""">free consultations</strong> to evaluate your situation confidentially</li><li id="""">Help you navigate EEOC filings, timelines, and what evidence you need</li><li id="""">Build a case that reflects the harm you’ve experienced—emotionally and financially</li><li id="""">Represent you with integrity, compassion, and strength</li></ul><p id="""">We don’t just file paperwork—we fight for justice. Our firm has helped countless North Alabama residents who’ve been wrongfully terminated due to race, and we’re ready to help you take the next step forward.</p><h3 id=""""><strong id="""">Don’t Wait. Speak Up.</strong></h3><p id="""">If you believe you’ve been fired or mistreated because of your race, or if you’ve been punished for reporting bias, now is the time to act. The sooner you <a href=""https://www.defattalaw.com/free-consultation"">contact <strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong></a>, the sooner we can begin investigating and protecting your rights.</p><p id="""">‍</p>",https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/656a0c175024d9fe2bb6d05f/681fb54b6fb5bcbcf4343286_discrimination_1.png,alix-defatta
"Slip and Fall Accidents in Huntsville, Alabama: Who’s Really at Fault?",slip-and-fall-accidents-in-huntsville-alabama,65ef12146fbd9a8bbf3c7fb0,65ef12146fbd9a8bbf3c7f9f,67f95e77ab1bc72b791e2e62,false,false,Fri Apr 11 2025 18:24:55 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time),Fri Apr 11 2025 19:23:28 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time),Fri Apr 11 2025 19:23:28 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time),,"<p id=""""><strong id="""">Slip and Fall Accidents in Huntsville, Alabama: Who’s Really at Fault?</strong></p><p id="""">Slip and fall accidents are among the most common personal injury claims in <strong id="""">Huntsville, Alabama</strong>—but that doesn’t mean they’re simple to resolve. Whether it happened at a grocery store, restaurant, apartment complex, or parking lot, determining <em id="""">who’s really at fault</em> isn’t always black and white. At <a href=""https://www.defattalaw.com/free-consultation""><strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong></a>, we help clients across <strong id="""">North Alabama</strong> understand their rights and recover compensation when negligence plays a role.<br></p><p id="""">Let’s break it down:</p><h3 id=""""><strong id="""">What Is Premises Liability?</strong></h3><p id="""">Premises liability refers to a property owner’s legal responsibility to maintain safe conditions on their property. Under Alabama law, property owners have a <em id="""">duty of care</em> to visitors, especially customers or invited guests. When they fail to fix or warn about a hazardous condition—and someone gets hurt—they can be held liable.<br></p><p id="""">Common causes of slip and fall accidents include:</p><ul id=""""><li id="""">Wet or slippery floors</li><li id="""">Uneven pavement or sidewalks</li><li id="""">Broken handrails</li><li id="""">Poor lighting</li><li id="""">Debris or obstacles in walkways<br></li></ul><p id="""">If the hazard was known—or should have been known—by the property owner, they may be held accountable for the injuries sustained.</p><h3 id=""""><strong id="""">When Are Property Owners Legally Responsible?</strong></h3><p id="""">A successful slip and fall claim hinges on <strong id="""">proving negligence</strong>. That means showing the property owner:</p><ol start=""1"" id=""""><li id="""">Knew (or should’ve known) about the dangerous condition</li><li id="""">Had a reasonable amount of time to fix it or post a warning</li><li id="""">Failed to take appropriate action<br></li></ol><p id="""">In Alabama, property owners owe different levels of care depending on the visitor’s legal status (invitee, licensee, or trespasser). Most slip and fall victims are considered invitees—people who are on the property for the owner’s benefit (like shoppers or tenants).<br></p><p id="""">Here’s the tricky part: <strong id="""">Alabama follows contributory negligence laws.</strong> If the injured person is found even <em id="""">slightly</em> at fault for their fall, they could be barred from recovering compensation. That’s why it’s so important to have an experienced legal team on your side.</p><h3 id=""""><strong id="""">Navigating Unclear Liability with DeFatta Law Firm</strong></h3><p id="""">At <strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong>, we know how complex these cases can be. Maybe there were no warning signs posted. Maybe surveillance footage conveniently disappeared. Or maybe you’re being blamed for not “watching where you were going.” We’ve seen it all—and we know how to build a strong case backed by evidence and expert analysis.<br></p><p id="""">Whether your accident happened in a retail store in <strong id="""">Huntsville</strong>, a local apartment complex, or anywhere in <strong id="""">North Alabama</strong>, we’ll help you determine:</p><ul id=""""><li id="""">If the property owner breached their duty of care</li><li id="""">Whether your injury qualifies under premises liability</li><li id="""">What evidence is needed to prove your case</li><li id="""">How much compensation you may be entitled to</li></ul><h3 id=""""><strong id="""">What to Do After a Slip and Fall in Huntsville</strong></h3><p id="""">If you’ve been hurt in a slip and fall accident, take these steps as soon as possible:</p><ol start=""1"" id=""""><li id=""""><strong id="""">Seek medical attention</strong> – Your health comes first, and documentation is key.</li><li id=""""><strong id="""">Report the incident</strong> – Alert the manager or property owner and ask for a written report.</li><li id=""""><strong id="""">Take photos</strong> – Capture the hazard, location, and your injuries if possible.</li><li id=""""><strong id="""">Gather witness info</strong> – Names and contact details are invaluable.</li><li id=""""><strong id="""">Call DeFatta Law Firm</strong> – The sooner you get legal guidance, the better your chances of a successful claim.</li></ol><h3 id=""""><strong id="""">Let DeFatta Law Firm Stand Up for You</strong></h3><p id="""">No one expects a quick trip to the store or a walk through their apartment hallway to end in injury—but when it does, you deserve to understand your legal options. At <strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong>, we’re committed to helping slip and fall victims across <strong id="""">Huntsville</strong> and <strong id="""">North Alabama</strong> get the justice and compensation they deserve.</p><p id=""""><strong id="""">Don’t wait—</strong><a href=""https://www.defattalaw.com/free-consultation""><strong id="""">contact DeFatta Law Firm today</strong> for a free consultation</a>. Let’s hold negligent property owners accountable and get you back on your feet.</p><p id="""">‍</p>",https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/656a0c175024d9fe2bb6d05f/67f95e70c60edab9ce485b93_slip_fall_defatta_law_1.png,phil-defatta
Summer Motorcycle Safety in North Alabama: What Every Rider Should Know,summer-motorcycle,65ef12146fbd9a8bbf3c7fb0,65ef12146fbd9a8bbf3c7f9f,689124acd61b0af03d51114d,false,false,Mon Aug 04 2025 21:22:52 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time),Mon Aug 04 2025 21:26:01 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time),Mon Aug 04 2025 21:26:01 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time),"There’s nothing quite like hitting the open road on a motorcycle during a warm Huntsville, Alabama summer day. But with rising temperatures also comes a rise in serious motorcycle accidents across North Alabama. At DeFatta Law Firm, we want riders to enjoy the season—without becoming a statistic.","<p id="""">There’s nothing quite like hitting the open road on a motorcycle during a warm <strong id="""">Huntsville, Alabama</strong> summer day. But with rising temperatures also comes a rise in serious motorcycle accidents across <strong id="""">North Alabama</strong>. At <a href=""https://www.defattalaw.com/free-consultation""><strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong></a>, we want riders to enjoy the season—without becoming a statistic.</p><h2 id=""""><strong id="""">Why Summer Is More Dangerous for Motorcyclists</strong><br></h2><p id="""">While warm weather means more riding days, it also increases risk. Here’s why:</p><ul id=""""><li><strong id="""">Traffic Volume Increases</strong>: Summer brings out more cars, tourists, and teen drivers.</li><li><strong id="""">Inexperienced Riders</strong>: Many motorcyclists only ride seasonally and may be rusty.</li><li><strong id="""">Heat Stress</strong>: Dehydration and fatigue can affect reaction time.</li><li><strong id="""">Sun Glare</strong>: Especially around dusk, visibility becomes a serious hazard.</li></ul><h2 id=""""><strong id="""">Top Summer Motorcycle Safety Tips for North Alabama Riders</strong><br></h2><p id="""">At <a href=""https://www.defattalaw.com/free-consultation""><strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong></a>, we’ve seen too many preventable motorcycle crashes. Here’s how to reduce your risk:</p><ul id=""""><li><strong id="""">Always Wear Protective Gear</strong>: Even when it’s hot. A helmet, gloves, boots, and a jacket can save your life.</li><li><strong id="""">Hydrate Often</strong>: Heat exhaustion can hit quickly on long rides.</li><li><strong id="""">Use Sunscreen</strong>: Exposed skin can burn fast on long sunny rides.</li><li><strong id="""">Make Yourself Seen</strong>: Wear reflective vests or bright colors. Use daytime running lights.</li><li><strong id="""">Obey the Speed Limit</strong>: Especially on winding backroads throughout North Alabama.</li><li><strong id="""">Assume You’re Invisible</strong>: Don’t count on other drivers to spot you.</li><li><strong id="""">Do a Safety Check</strong>: Tires, brakes, signals, and fluids should all be inspected before a ride.</li><li><strong id="""">Avoid Riding at Night</strong>: Visibility drops and wildlife becomes a bigger risk.</li><li><strong id="""">Watch the Road Surface</strong>: Summer means more grass clippings, oil slicks, and loose gravel—any of which can send a bike flying.</li></ul><h2 id=""""><strong id="""">What to Do After a Motorcycle Crash in Huntsville or North Alabama</strong><br></h2><p id="""">If you’re involved in a motorcycle accident, protect yourself legally and medically:</p><ol start=""1"" id=""""><li><strong id="""">Get to Safety</strong> – Out of traffic if possible.</li><li><strong id="""">Call 911</strong> – Even if you think you’re okay.</li><li><strong id="""">Document the Scene</strong> – Take photos, collect witness info, and get a police report.</li><li><strong id="""">Seek Medical Care</strong> – Some injuries don’t show up right away.</li><li><strong id="""">Contact DeFatta Law Firm</strong> – Our team in <strong id="""">Huntsville, Alabama</strong> can help you navigate your injury claim.</li></ol><h2 id=""""><strong id="""">How DeFatta Law Firm Supports Motorcycle Injury Victims</strong><br></h2><p id="""">We know how serious motorcycle crashes can be. At <strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong>, we’ve helped victims across <strong id="""">North Alabama </strong>recover compensation for:</p><ul id=""""><li>Medical bills</li><li>Lost wages</li><li>Pain and suffering</li><li>Long-term disability</li><li>Wrongful death claims<br></li></ul><p id="""">We deal with the legal stress so you can focus on healing. And we don’t get paid unless you win.</p><p id="""">Summer should be a time of freedom and fun—not fear and recovery. Whether you’re riding through the <strong id="""">Huntsville city streets</strong> or the rural highways of <strong id="""">North Alabama</strong>, take steps to protect yourself. And if the worst happens, know that <strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong> is ready to help.</p><p id=""""><strong id="""">Injured in a motorcycle accident? </strong><a href=""https://www.defattalaw.com/free-consultation""><strong id="""">Contact DeFatta Law Firm today for a free consultation</strong></a><strong id="""">.</strong></p><p>‍</p>",https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/656a0c175024d9fe2bb6d05f/68912563285ce6e6024f84be_motorsummer.png,alix-defatta
"The Dangers of Distracted Driving in Huntsville, Alabama — and How DeFatta Law Firm Can Help Victims",the-dangers-of-distracted-driving,65ef12146fbd9a8bbf3c7fb0,65ef12146fbd9a8bbf3c7f9f,680d2a29fde87f222439e6b3,false,false,Sat Apr 26 2025 18:47:05 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time),Wed Apr 30 2025 17:25:17 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time),Wed Apr 30 2025 17:25:17 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time),"Distracted driving isn’t just careless — it’s dangerous. Every day in Huntsville, Alabama and across North Alabama, lives are shattered because someone couldn’t keep their eyes, hands, or mind on the road.","<p id="""">Distracted driving isn’t just careless — it’s dangerous. Every day in <strong id="""">Huntsville, Alabama</strong> and across <strong id="""">North Alabama</strong>, lives are shattered because someone couldn’t keep their eyes, hands, or mind on the road.</p><p id="""">At <strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong>, we know how devastating these accidents can be for victims and their families. That’s why we fight tirelessly to hold distracted drivers accountable — and help our clients rebuild their lives after a crash.</p><h3 id=""""><strong id="""">What Counts as Distracted Driving?</strong></h3><p id="""">Distracted driving is any activity that diverts a driver’s attention from operating their vehicle safely. Some of the most common distractions we see in <strong id="""">Huntsville</strong> and <strong id="""">North Alabama</strong> include:</p><ul id=""""><li><strong id="""">Texting or checking social media</strong></li><li><strong id="""">Using a GPS or navigation system</strong></li><li><strong id="""">Eating or drinking</strong> behind the wheel</li><li><strong id="""">Changing music or podcasts</strong></li><li><strong id="""">Talking to passengers</strong></li></ul><p id="""">Texting while driving is especially deadly. It takes your eyes off the road for an average of five seconds — long enough to travel the length of a football field at 55 mph.</p><p id="""">At <strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong>, we know how quickly a momentary distraction can cause lifelong injuries or even wrongful death. That’s why we treat distracted driving cases with the seriousness they deserve.</p><h3 id=""""><strong id="""">How Victims Can Prove Distracted Driving Negligence</strong></h3><p id="""">Insurance companies often try to deny that a driver was distracted. That’s why it’s critical to gather strong evidence early. When you work with <strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong> in <strong id="""">Huntsville, Alabama</strong>, we immediately begin building your case by:</p><ul id=""""><li><strong id="""">Requesting cellphone records</strong> to show texting or app use at the time of the accident</li><li><strong id="""">Obtaining police reports</strong> that document driver distraction</li><li><strong id="""">Interviewing witnesses</strong> who saw the at-fault driver texting, eating, or otherwise distracted</li><li><strong id="""">Collecting surveillance or dashcam footage</strong> whenever available</li><li><strong id="""">Consulting accident reconstruction experts</strong> if needed</li></ul><p id="""">We leave no stone unturned to prove negligence and fight for the compensation our clients in <strong id="""">North Alabama</strong> deserve.</p><h3 id=""""><strong id="""">The Real Costs of Distracted Driving Accidents</strong></h3><p id="""">A distracted driver’s careless decision can leave innocent people facing:</p><ul id=""""><li>Emergency room visits and hospital stays</li><li>Long-term rehabilitation</li><li>Permanent disabilities</li><li>Lost income and reduced earning potential</li><li>Pain, emotional trauma, and diminished quality of life</li></ul><p id="""">At <strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong>, we understand the real, human cost of distracted driving. That’s why we fight for full and fair compensation — not just for your current bills, but for your future needs, too.</p><h3 id=""""><strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm: Fighting for Victims Across North Alabama</strong></h3><p id="""">When you’re the victim of a distracted driving accident, you deserve a law firm that knows how to win — and that treats you with the care and respect you deserve.</p><p id="""">At <strong id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</strong> in <strong id="""">Huntsville, Alabama</strong>, we take pride in standing up for injury victims across <strong id="""">North Alabama</strong>. We know how to cut through insurance company excuses and demand real accountability.</p><p id=""""><strong id="""">Contact DeFatta Law Firm today</strong> for a free consultation. Let us take the burden off your shoulders so you can focus on healing — while we focus on getting you the justice and compensation you’re entitled to.</p><p>‍</p>",https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/656a0c175024d9fe2bb6d05f/680d2a1fd79e341aa558c042_texting_driving_1.png,alix-defatta
"The Psychology of Pain: How Chronic Injuries Affect Mental Health and Your Legal Case in Huntsville, Alabama",the-psychology-of-pain,65ef12146fbd9a8bbf3c7fb0,65ef12146fbd9a8bbf3c7f9f,6786c3fdb5cce2ced6d91723,false,false,Tue Jan 14 2025 20:07:25 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time),Tue Jan 14 2025 20:08:09 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time),Fri Apr 11 2025 22:53:20 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time),"When you've been injured in an accident, the physical pain is often just the beginning of your journey. At DeFatta Law Firm, we've witnessed countless clients struggle not only with their bodily injuries but also with the profound psychological impact that follows. While many people focus solely on physical recovery, the mental health aspects of chronic injuries can be equally devastating and deserve just as much attention in your legal case.","<p id="""">When you've been injured in an accident, the physical pain is often just the beginning of your journey. At <a href=""https://www.defattalaw.com/free-consultation"" id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</a>, we've witnessed countless clients struggle not only with their bodily injuries but also with the profound psychological impact that follows. While many people focus solely on physical recovery, the mental health aspects of chronic injuries can be equally devastating and deserve just as much attention in your legal case.</p><p>‍</p><h1 id="""">Understanding the Mental Health Impact</h1><p>‍</p><p id="""">Chronic pain and serious injuries can trigger a cascade of mental health challenges that many victims don't anticipate. These often include:</p><p>‍</p><h2 id="""">Depression and Anxiety</h2><p id="""">The constant presence of pain can lead to feelings of helplessness and hopelessness. Many of our clients at <a href=""https://www.defattalaw.com/free-consultation"" id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</a> report experiencing persistent anxiety about their future, especially when facing uncertain recovery timelines or financial pressures from medical bills and lost wages.</p><p>‍</p><h2 id="""">Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)</h2><p id="""">PTSD isn't limited to combat veterans or natural disaster survivors. After a serious accident, many individuals develop PTSD symptoms such as:</p><p id="""">- Flashbacks of the accident</p><p id="""">- Severe anxiety when passing the accident location</p><p id="""">- Nightmares and sleep disturbances</p><p id="""">- Avoidance behaviors related to the accident circumstances</p><p>‍</p><h2 id="""">Relationship Strain</h2><p id="""">Chronic pain can significantly impact your relationships. The attorneys at DeFatta Law Firm often hear from clients struggling with:</p><p id="""">- Decreased social interaction due to physical limitations</p><p id="""">- Strain on marriages and partnerships</p><p id="""">- Difficulty maintaining friendships</p><p id="""">- Challenges in caring for children or elderly parents</p><p>‍</p><h1 id="""">The Hidden Costs of Psychological Impact</h1><p>‍</p><p id="""">What many don't realize is that the mental health consequences of an injury often outlast the physical symptoms. These psychological effects can lead to:</p><p id="""">- Lost productivity at work</p><p id="""">- Increased medical expenses for mental health treatment</p><p id="""">- Need for long-term therapy or counseling</p><p id="""">- Prescription medication costs for psychological conditions</p><p id="""">- Reduced quality of life</p><p>‍</p><h1 id="""">How <a href=""https://www.defattalaw.com/free-consultation"" id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</a> Advocates for Your Mental Health</h1><p>‍</p><p id="""">At DeFatta Law Firm, we understand that a comprehensive injury claim must address both physical and psychological damages. Our approach includes:</p><p>‍</p><h2 id="""">Documentation and Evidence</h2><p id="""">We work with mental health professionals to thoroughly document how your injury has affected your psychological well-being. This might include:</p><p id="""">- Professional assessments from psychiatrists or psychologists</p><p id="""">- Documentation of prescribed medications for mental health conditions</p><p id="""">- Therapy session records</p><p id="""">- Expert testimony about long-term psychological impacts</p><p>‍</p><h2 id="""">Comprehensive Compensation Claims</h2><p id="""">Our legal team ensures that your compensation claim includes:</p><p id="""">- Costs of mental health treatment</p><p id="""">- Therapy and counseling expenses</p><p id="""">- Lost wages due to psychological challenges</p><p id="""">- Compensation for emotional distress and mental anguish</p><p id="""">- Future projected mental health care costs</p><p>‍</p><h2 id="""">Insurance Company Tactics</h2><p>‍</p><p id="""">Insurance companies often try to minimize or dismiss psychological damages, claiming they're unrelated to the accident. <a href=""https://www.defattalaw.com/free-consultation"" id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</a>'s experienced attorneys know how to counter these tactics by:</p><p id="""">- Presenting clear evidence linking mental health issues to the accident</p><p id="""">- Demonstrating the impact on daily life and relationships</p><p id="""">- Providing expert testimony about long-term psychological effects</p><p id="""">- Showing how mental health challenges affect earning capacity</p><p>‍</p><h1 id="""">Steps to Protect Your Mental Health After an Injury</h1><p>‍</p><h2 id="""">1. Seek Professional Help Early</h2><p id="""">Don't wait for psychological symptoms to become severe. Early intervention can prevent long-term mental health challenges.</p><p>‍</p><h2 id="""">2. Document Everything</h2><p id="""">Keep a journal of your mental health symptoms and how they affect your daily life. This documentation can be valuable evidence in your case.</p><p>‍</p><h2 id="""">3. Follow Treatment Plans</h2><p id="""">Attend all recommended therapy sessions and take prescribed medications as directed.</p><p>‍</p><h2 id="""">4. Communicate with Your Legal Team</h2><p id="""">Keep DeFatta Law Firm informed about your psychological symptoms and treatment. This helps us build a stronger case for comprehensive compensation.</p><p>‍</p><h1 id="""">Looking Forward</h1><p>‍</p><p id="""">Recovery from a serious injury is a journey that affects both body and mind. At <a href=""https://www.defattalaw.com/free-consultation"" id="""">DeFatta Law Firm</a>, we're committed to helping you navigate both aspects of your recovery. Our experienced attorneys understand the complex interplay between physical injuries and mental health, and we fight tirelessly to ensure you receive the compensation you deserve for all aspects of your injury.</p><p>‍</p><p id="""">Don't let insurance companies minimize your mental health struggles. If you're dealing with the psychological aftermath of an injury, contact DeFatta Law Firm today. We'll help you understand your rights and options for securing compensation that addresses both your physical and mental well-being.</p><p>‍</p><p id="""">Remember: Your mental health is just as important as your physical health, and at DeFatta Law Firm, we're here to protect both.</p><p>‍<a href=""https://www.defattalaw.com/free-consultation"" id="""">Contact DeFatta Law Firm</a> today for a free consultation to discuss how we can help you navigate the complex intersection of personal injury and mental health. Your recovery – both physical and psychological – is our priority.</p>",https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/656a0c175024d9fe2bb6d05f/6786c3f6b5cce2ced6d90c52_stressed%205%207x5.png,phil-defatta
The Top 5 Ways Huntsville Drivers Crash Their Cars (and How Not to Be One of Them),how-to-avoid-car-crashes,65ef12146fbd9a8bbf3c7fb0,65ef12146fbd9a8bbf3c7f9f,65ef12146fbd9a8bbf3c803f,false,false,Sat Feb 03 2024 02:01:21 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time),Sat Feb 03 2024 02:01:40 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time),Mon Mar 11 2024 14:32:07 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time),"Fender benders, rear endings, t-bones - accidents happen all too often on Huntsville’s busy streets. But many crashes are preventable if you know the most accident-prone driving behaviors.","<p id="""">Fender benders, rear endings, t-bones - accidents happen all too often on Huntsville’s busy streets. But many crashes are preventable if you know the most accident-prone driving behaviors. DeFatta Law Firm is here to clue you in on the top ways Huntsville motorists ruin their rides so you can avoid joining the not-so-prestigious club.</p><p id="""">1. Rubbernecking roadside wrecks</p><p id="""">We get it, crumpled metal and flashing lights draws the eye like bees to honey. But gawking at accident scenes leads to more accidents if drivers don’t pay attention to the road. So flex that neck away from the distraction and keep your eyes forward before you cause another wreck. The police have it handled - move along.</p><p id="""">2. Playing bumper cars in rush hour </p><p id="""">The commute on I-565 can get tighter than skinny jeans on Fashion Week. But no matter how slowly the traffic creeps, it’s never justification for drivers playing bumper cars. Maintain a safe following distance and stay alert. The second you let your mind wander, you’ll likely have a bumper sticker imprinted on your hood.</p><p id="""">3. Driving like you’re storming the Daytona 500</p><p id="""">Speed limits seem like mere suggestions to some lead-footed Huntsville drivers who feel the need for speed. But hurtling down Jordan Lane like it’s the Daytona 500 increases the risk of dangerous wrecks. Slow your roll and remind yourself you’re not an Andretti (or Earnhardt). The few minutes you’ll shave off your drive isn’t worth endangering everyone.</p><p id="""">4. Cruising whilst snoozing</p><p id="""">Drowsy driving accounts for as many accidents as drunk driving. So don’t get behind the wheel if you’re cruising for a snoozing. If you feel your eyelids getting heavy, pull over and get some rest or caffeine. Trying to push through and drive while fatigued can have dire consequences. Take a nap - your destination will still be there when you wake up.</p><p id="""">5. Semi-driving while distracted </p><p id="""">Texting, eating, grooming - drivers seemingly can’t resist the temptation to multitask in the car. But distracted driving significantly raises your crash risk. So keep your hands on the wheel and your eyes on the road. Your texts will still be there after you park. Don’t drive inattentively and contribute to Huntsville’s accident woes.</p><p id="""">Use your noodle and avoid these all-too-common accident causes whenever you drive around Huntsville. And if the worst happens, call DeFatta Law Firm. Our experienced attorneys will deal with the insurance companies so you can focus on recovering from your injuries. Just try to steer clear of our specialty by being an attentive driver!</p><p id="""">‍</p>",https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/656a0c175024d9fe2bb6d05f/65bd9e5cf4d75747592e327a_fender.png,phil-defatta
